    <stitle>7 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS FULLER SERIES - REMOVE - REAR HOUSING</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="IDcomponent" graphiccount="5">
        <title>REAR HOUSING</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove bolts and both countershaft rear bearing covers (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302511">Figure 11</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f1302511" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g1302511" filename="../figg13/G1302511.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
            <caption>Figure 11. Remove Countershaft Rear Bearing Covers</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove bolts and the output shaft rear bearing cover (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302512">Figure 12</hotlnk>). If necessary, remove the oil seal from the cover (inset).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f1302512" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g1302512" filename="../figg13/G1302512.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
            <caption>Figure 12. Remove Output Shaft Rear Bearing Cover</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the spacer from the output shaft (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302513">Figure 13</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f1302513" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g1302513" filename="../figg13/G1302513.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
            <caption>Figure 13. Remove Spacer From Output Shaft</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the rear housing retaining bolts (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302514">Figure 14</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f1302514" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g1302514" filename="../figg13/G1302514.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
            <caption>Figure 14. Remove Rear Housing Retaining Bolts</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install three 4-inch bolts in the three tapped holes in the rear plate and tighten evenly to
                move the housing to the rear (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302515">Figure 15</hotlnk>). Remove the bolts.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f1302515" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g1302515" filename="../figg13/G1302515.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
            <caption>Figure 15. Install Bolts and Tighten Evenly</caption>
        </figure>
    </svcproc>
